I"	<p>135 homes are earmarked for demolition on Lambethâ€™s Geoffrey Close estate - otherwise known as the Lambeth estate.</p>

<p>Housing association Riverside Homes, which manages the estate, <a href="https://www.riverside.org.uk/redevelopment-projects/lambeth-estate-revitalising-your-neighbourhood/about-the-redevelopment-of-the-lambeth-estate/">wants to replace it</a> with 400 new homes, 135 of which at London Affordable Rent.</p>

<p>In December 2018, 67% of residents who voted in the ballot voted in favour of redevelopment. The scheme is being <a href="/approved/funding">funded</a> by the Mayor in a joint venture between Riverside and Bellway Homes.</p>

